  "text": "Recent preclinical and clinical studies have demonstrated that Salacia roots modulate multiple targets: peroxisome proliferator activated receptor-alpha-mediated lipogenic gene transcription [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , angiotensin II/angiotensin II type 1 receptor [CITATION_3] , alpha-glucosidase, aldose reductase, and pancreatic lipase [CITATION_4] . These multitarget actions may mainly contribute to Salacia root-induced improvement of type 2 diabetes and obesity-associated hyperglycemia, dyslipidemia, and related cardiovascular complications seen in humans and rodents.",
